The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Going by SAI, Eastern Region director P. C. Kashyap, the city is set to have its own international standard swimming pool by July next year. SAI has already started the construction of the pool in its Salt Lake campus, which will have all the amenities required to stage an international event.

 The pool ? for which Rs 2 crore has been sanctioned ? is a part of the first phase of an Aquatic Complex to be built over an area of 2.5 acres. SAI officials have asked for another Rs 3.5 cores from the government for the ambitious project.

 Besides the international standard pool, the complex will have separate pool for kids and learners and also a diving pool and multi-gym.

 Thirteen teams are going to take part in an inter-school basketball tournament being organised by the Women?s Basketball Association of West Bengal at Loreto House from Monday. 

 The meet will be played in three categories ? mini, junior and senior. 

